  "prompt": "What are the top 10 sightseeing sites in and near Chandigarh?",
  "response": "Here are the top 10 sightseeing sites in and near Chandigarh:\n\n1. Rock Garden\n- Created by Nek Chand\n- Unique sculpture garden with art made from industrial waste\n- Famous for creative and imaginative displays\n\n2. Sukhna Lake\n- Artificial lake in the heart of the city\n- Popular for morning walks and boating\n- Scenic and peaceful environment\n\n3. Rose Garden\n- Largest rose garden in Asia\n- Over 1,600 different rose varieties\n- Beautiful landscape and flower displays\n\n4. Chandigarh Museum and Art Gallery\n- Exhibits Gandhara sculptures and miniature paintings\n- Showcases rich cultural heritage\n- Modern architectural design\n\n5. Capitol Complex\n- UNESCO World Heritage Site\n- Designed by Le Corbusier\n- Impressive government buildings and architectural marvel\n\n6. Pinjore Gardens\n- Historical Mughal-style gardens\n- Located near Chandigarh\n- Beautiful landscaping and fountains\n\n7. Timber Trail, Parwanoo\n- Scenic cable car ride\n- Panoramic Himalayan views\n- Located near Chandigarh\n\n8. Morni Hills\n- Nearby hill station\n- Natural scenic beauty\n- Ideal for trekking and nature walks\n\n9. International Dolls Museum\n- Large collection of dolls from around the world\n- Unique and interesting attraction\n\n10. Cactus Garden\n- Largest succulent garden in India\n- Diverse cactus species\n- Educational and visually appealing",
